1207. hominem, the accusative of exclamation or specification. The important position which the accusative case acquired in late Latin is shewn by such uses as lzic quiescunt duas nostrates (Inscription from Africa), and the fact that Romance language forms regularly come from the accusative, e.g. pied: pedem, nuitmzoctem, rien=rem. Similarly the Latins in transferring Greek words to their language usually took the accusative, e.g.
